    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-10-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="386" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Coggeshall</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 12.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United States Legation,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-10-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 28, 1866</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to advise you that the
                            question of the transfer of the Gallapagos islands has been reviewed
                            before the government of Ecuador, by a proposition for their purchase
                            from the British holders of Ecuadorian bonds. Such sale direct is
                            forbidden by the Constitution of Ecuador, and by treaty stipulations,
                            but the expediency of such a transfer, at a price to be agreed upon
                            between the contracting parties, as will put the British bondholders in
                            possession of the islands <hi rend="italic">de facto,</hi> and yet
                            conserve the political jurisdiction of Ecuador, has been urgently
                            presented to the cabinet of this republic, and is now, I am credibly
                            informed, a topic of official correspondence.</p>
                <p>Very respectfully, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. T. COGGESHALL.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington, D. C</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
